cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with automated medical image analysis using deep learning techniques, specifically for brain tumor segmentation and survival day prediction. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of conditional Generative Adversarial Network (cGAN) and adversarial training also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also mentions the BraTS 2017 segmentation and prediction tasks, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
